examples.en: She did a painting of the region's rugged coastline.
Our state is now the region's leading economic power.
The usual weekend traffic congested the region's highways.
A third of the region's population still lives off the land.
The region's heavy industry is still inefficient and moribund.
This is one of the region's most important archeological sites.
Forecasters predict the region's economy is heading for disaster.
The tourist industry forms a crucial part of the region's economic equation.
The company has tried to insulate itself from the region's political turmoil.
For a short while (=a short time), the city functioned as the region's capital.
This class is designed to acquaint students with the region's most important writers.
Martha is now one of the region's leading businesswomen, with a chain of successful salons.
They warned that casino gambling would not be an elixir for all of the region's economic woes.
The newspaper will be making some changes in order to adapt to the region's shifting demographics.
For a long time the aboriginals were not even included in the censuses, as they were viewed as part of the region's fauna.
